en_723748_0	The Colombo High Court was informed today that the President and the Prime Minister are agreeable under certain conditions to end the proceedings in the shortest manner with regard to the case filed against former parliamentarian TissaAttanayake for allegedly forging their signatures.
en_723748_1	The parties requested the court to grant a future date in order to facilitate the completion of the case in a shorter time frame.
en_723748_2	Further court was informed that if the accused was willing to apologize for his acts the Prime Minister and the President were willing to end the case in the shortest possible proceeding.
en_723748_3	The case will be taken up again for further hearing on April 24th.
